The paper deals with the planarity and crossing properties of graphs, which are central topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of operations such as s-subdivision, path-addition, and node-to-circle expansion suggests a focus on graph theory (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.GT). Finally, the paper also touches on the recognition problem for fan-crossing free graphs, which is a classic problem in computational complexity (cs.SI).
